    <item>
      <title>Re: Customer Service lacking</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&amp;message.id=3347#M3347</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Thanks for the patience folks!&amp;nbsp; Here is something from CS about CS support.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The in-game petition system is designed so that Customer Service can assist our customers with in-game issues in the most efficient manner and in the fairest way possible; the order they are received.&amp;nbsp; It is also designed to track all customer tickets and the details regarding them so there is documentation of the issue being petitioned and how this was addressed by the GM (it helps a GM greatly to resolve an ongoing issue if they have access to any notes on what was done before they received the petition).&amp;nbsp; CS also uses the data provided by petitions submitted in the different category types in order to identify new issues and to assign GMs to work on specific categories of petitions when necessary, with the goal of maintaining the fastest possible response times and the highest quality of service overall.&amp;nbsp; By analyzing the number of petitions in each category/subcategory, we can adjust our focus on the ticket queues and address your issues faster.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;This is why it is required to submit a request for assistance through the in-game petition system for in-game issues instead of sending a request for help via email, the forums, or any other way.&amp;nbsp; If GMs were to address regular in-game issues in other manners, not only would customers be assisted out of turn in an unorganized fashion, the documentation and ticket information would be scattered across several systems and would slow down the process of helping customers tremendously.&amp;nbsp; For these reasons, it is very important not to circumvent the petition system.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If&amp;nbsp;you have complaints regarding the quality of service&amp;nbsp;you have received,&amp;nbsp;we ask that you&amp;nbsp;email &lt;A href="mailto:eqcs@soe.sony.com" target=_blank&gt;eqcs@soe.sony.com&lt;/A&gt; with the details of the complaint and the ticket number of the petition&amp;nbsp;you submitted regarding the original issue.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Very important note regarding this email address: This email address is not intended as an alternative method to the in-game petition system and should only be used for complaints regarding quality of service based on the following:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Rude, impolite, or inappropriate behavior of a GM &lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Inappropriate use of a template response&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Please understand that the resolution to the issue you originally petitioned about may not be changed as the intent of this point of contact is&amp;nbsp;to give&amp;nbsp;customers&amp;nbsp;a method to&amp;nbsp;report complaints so that CS Management can investigate and address any issues found.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Should you send a complaint to this email address, a CS supervisor will be investigating the actions of the GM for any inappropriate behavior and will take corrective action should they find a need, however decisions made by a GM acting in accordance with our policies will not be changed.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The &lt;A href="mailto:eqcs@soe.sony.com" target=_blank&gt;eqcs@soe.sony.com&lt;/A&gt; email address can also be used to offer feedback and suggestions regarding ways to improve our ticketing system.&amp;nbsp; Feedback and suggestion emails, while important to us and often quite useful, will most likely not receive a response.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
